text: Larsmo () is a municipality in Ostrobothnia, Finland. It is along the Gulf of Bothnia. As of 31 December 2023, 5,843 people lived there. Neighbouring municipalities are Jakobstad, Kokkola, Kronoby and Pedersöre. About 90% of the people speak Swedish. About 5% of the people speak Finnish. It was founded in 1867. == Other websites == * Municipality of Larsmo – Official website Category:1867 establishments in Finland Category:Municipalities of Ostrobothnia
